<script>
  import { Button, Link, Tag, Card } from '@gsa-tts/svelte-ui-uswds';
  
  let count = $state(0);
</script>

# Interactive Components in Markdown

One of the powerful features of mdsvex is the ability to embed Svelte components directly in your markdown content.

## Buttons

You can add interactive buttons:

<Button onclick={() => count++}>
  Clicked {count} times
</Button>

<Button variant="secondary" onclick={() => count = 0}>
  Reset
</Button>

The count is: **{count}**

## Links

Links can be styled with USWDS classes:

<Link href="https://designsystem.digital.gov" variant="external">
  USWDS Documentation
</Link>

Or use regular markdown links, which are automatically converted to Link components:

Visit the [Svelte documentation](https://svelte.dev) for more information.

## Tags

Tags are useful for labeling and categorization:

<Tag>Important</Tag>
<Tag>New Feature</Tag>
<Tag>Documentation</Tag>

## Cards

Cards can organize content in a structured way:

<Card>
  {#snippet children()}
    <h3>Card Title</h3>
    <p>This is a card with some content inside. Cards are great for organizing information.</p>
  {/snippet}
</Card>

